After a successful maiden edition of Humour awards 2021, themed The Revolution, organisers of the event have unveiled the theme of the 2022 edition of the awards. Though the date of the 2022 edition is yet to be announced, organisers revealed this year’s edition’s theme as The Dream, The Glory.   The Short finale: AMAA, StarTimes splash $7,000 on four…     Shon Nerat aims at causing ripples with Afro Electro Vibe     film trainees graduate from Kunle Afolayan’s KAP Academy   Explaining what inspired the theme, the creator of the awards, Uche Dominic said that before the maiden edition, the idea of creating an award that would genuinely reward and celebrate comedians for their hard work was merely a dream, which was brought into reality in 2021. He added that the success of the maiden edition was a victory for the entire comedy industry; hence The Glory. The humour awards are currently one of the biggest comedy awards shows in Africa as the maiden edition was well attended by popular comedians and entertainment bigwigs in Nigeria. With the unveiling of the theme for the 2022 edition, the organisers of the awards ceremony have maintained their resolve and commitment to developing the comedy industry and putting Nigerian comedy on the global map.